  "sections": {
    "Intro": {
      "text": "Not to be confused with\ntyphus\n, a distinct disease caused by a different genera of bacteria\n",
      "subsections": {},
      "tables": [],
      "links": []
    },
    "Background": {
      "text": "Also known as \"enteric fever\" (of which paratyphoid fever is an additional subset)\nDiagnosed in 2% of febrile travelers and caused by\nSalmonella\nenterica serotype Typhi\n(formerly\nSalmonella typhi\n)\nserotype paratyphi A, B, and C\n[2]\nEndemic in Mexico, Indonesia, Peru, and the Indian subcontinent\nPrior vaccination does not exclude infection\nIncubation period 1-3 weeks with chronic carrier state defined as organism in urine or stool > 12 months\nChronic carrier state risk factors: biliary tract abnormalities\n[3]",
      "subsections": {},
      "tables": [],
      "links": [
        {
          "text": "Salmonella",
          "url": "https://wikem.org/wiki/Salmonella"
        }
      ]
    },
    "Clinical_Features": {
